OL,6,FHe said it was "more likely than not
OL,7,Fthat the driver suffered a temporary
OL,8,Floss of consciousness due to fainting
OL,9,Fat the wheel as a result of a medical
OL,10,Fcondition".
OL,12,FA decision had already been taken not
OL,13,Fto prosecute Mr Brooke because of
OL,14,Fevidence he had suffered a medical
OL,15,Fepisode.
