OL,6,F"After a review of all evidence, a
OL,7,Fdecision was made by the CPS not to
OL,8,Fbring any criminal charges in the
OL,9,Fmatter and following this decision,
OL,10,Fall evidence from the investigation
OL,11,Fwas then shared with the Coroner's
OL,12,FOffice to be considered during the
OL,13,Fcourse of the inquest."
OL,15,FThe inquest heard how , but had not
OL,16,Fbeen told to avoid driving and felt
OL,17,F"in control" that morning.
